etro station\n| image       = Shin-Osaka Station Midosuji Line (01) IMG 7386 20130824.JPG\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Midosuji Line station platform\n| other_name  = \n| address     = 5-15-5 Nishinakajima, [[Yodogawa-ku, Osaka]]\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|34|44|0.51|N|135|29|54.73|E|type:railwaystation_region:JP}}\n| operator    = [[Osaka Metro]]\n| line        = [[Mid\u014dsuji Line]]\n| platforms   =  \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = M13\n| opened      = 1964\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = 139,241 daily<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.kotsu.city.osaka.lg.jp/library/ct/kotsutyousa/20161108_subway_nt.pdf | title=\u8def\u7dda\u5225\u99c5\u5225\u4e57\u964d\u4eba\u54e1 | publisher=[[Osaka Municipal Transportation Bureau]] | date=November 8, 2016 | accessdate=May 6, 2017}}</ref>\n| pass_year   = FY2016\n| services    = \n}}\n===Station layout===\nThis [[Train station|station]] has one island platform with two tracks on the third level, located to the west of the platforms and tracks for the Shinkansen.\n{|table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 rowspan=3 valign=top|'''3F<br>Platform level'''\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\" width=100|Platform <span style=\"color:#e5171f\">'''1'''</span>\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray;\" width=400|[[Midosuji Line|<span style=\"color:#e5171f\">'''Midosuji Line'''</span>]] towards {{STN|Nakamozu}} <small>({{STN|Nishinakajima-Minamigata}})</small> \u2192\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 2px black;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Island platform]], doors will open on the right</small>\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Platform <span style=\"color:#e5171f\">'''2'''</span>\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|\u2190 <span style=\"color:#e5171f\">'''Midosuji Line'''</span> toward {{STN|Senri-Ch\u016b\u014d}} <small>({{STN|Higashi-Mikuni}})</small> \n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|'''2F'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Mezzanine\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Ticket gates, ticket/[[ICOCA]]/[[PiTaPa]] machines, station agent, restrooms<br>Passageways to JR and Shinkansen platforms\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=50 valign=top|'''G'''\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=100 valign=top|Street Level\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\" width=400 valign=top|Exit/Entrance\n|}\n\n{{Ja-rail-line|first=2|pfn=1|col=#e5171f|name=Mid\u014dsuji Line|dir=for Umeda, Namba, Tennoji, and Nakamozu}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|first=3|pfn=2|col=#e5171f|nidx=Mid\u014dsuji Line|dir=for Senri-Ch\u016b\u014d}}\n\n===Adjacent stations===\n{{J-railservice start}}\n{{J-route|route=Mid\u014dsuji Line (M13)|col=#e5171f|f=w}}\n{{J-rserv|service=-|previous={{STN|Higashi-Mikuni}} (M12)|next={{STN|Nishinakajima-Minamigata}} (M14)}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{-}}\n\n==Surrounding area==\n===Inside the station===\n*Nippon Travel Agency TiS Shin-Osaka\n*JR Tokai Tours Shin-Osaka Branch\n*Osaka Prefectural Police, Railway Police Force Shin-Osaka\n\n*Osaka Noren Meguri restaurant (in the paid area for the Shinkansen)\n\n===North===\n*Shin-Osaka Hankyu Building\n*[[Mielparque]] Osaka\n*Hotel La Foret Osaka\n*Via Inn Shin-Osaka West\n*Konami Sports Club\n\n===South===\n*[[Nissin Foods]]\n*Shin-Osaka Washington Hotel Plaza\n*Osaka Prefectural Police, Railway Police Force Headquarters\n\n===East (Hinode Side)===\n*Shin-Osaka Youth Hostel\n*Shin-Osaka Station Hotel\n*Life Corporation\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of railway stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Osaka Metro Midosuji Line Kita-Osaka Kyuko Railway Namboku Line|state=expanded}}\n{{T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen|state=expanded}}\n{{Sanyo Shinkansen|state=expanded}}\n{{JR Kyoto Line|state=expanded}}\n{{West Japan Railway Company Osaka Higashi Line|state=expanded}}\n{{Osaka transit|state=expanded}}\n}}\n\n{{Commons category|Shin-Osaka Station}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shin-Osaka}}\n[[Category:Osaka Metro stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Osaka]]\n[[Category:Sany\u014d Shinkansen]]\n[[Category:T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen]]\n[[Category:T\u014dkaid\u014d Main Line]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1964]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2019]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway and metro station in Osaka, Japan}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Shin-Osaka Station\n| native_name = \u65b0\u5927\u962a\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = Shin-\u014csaka Station.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Shin-Osaka station building in 2018\n| other_name  = \n| address     = 5 Nishinakajima, [[Yodogawa-ku, Osaka]]\n| country     = Japan\n| map_type    = Japan\n| coordinates = \n| operator    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[File:JR logo (west).svg|20px]] [[JR West]]\n* [[File:JR logo (central).svg|20px]] [[JR Central]]\n* [[File:Osaka_Metro_logo_2.svg|20px]] [[Osaka Metro]]\n }}\n| line        = \n| platforms   =  \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| opened      = \n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \n| pass_year   = \n| services    = \n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Shin-Osaka Station'''|\u65b0\u5927\u962a\u99c5|Shin-\u014csaka-eki}} is a railway station in [[Yodogawa-ku, Osaka]], Japan. It is the western terminus of the high-speed [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen]] line from Tokyo, and the eastern terminus of the [[San'y\u014d Shinkansen]]. The lines are physically joined, and many trains offer through service.\n\nShin-Osaka is about 3&nbsp;km from the older [[\u014csaka Station]]. The new station was built in 1964 to avoid the engineering difficulties of running [[Shinkansen]] lines into the center of the city. The [[JR Kyoto Line]] and subway [[Mid\u014dsuji Line]] provide convenient connections to other stations around the city center.\n\n==Lines==\n*[[JR Kyoto Line]] ([[T\u014dkaid\u014d Main Line]], [[West Japan Railway Company]] (JR West))\n*[[San'y\u014d Shinkansen]] (JR West)\n*[[Osaka Higashi Line]] (JR West)\n*[[T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen]] ([[Central Japan Railway Company]] (JR Central)\n*[[Osaka Municipal Subway]] [[Mid\u014dsuji Line]] (M13)\n\n==JR==\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Shin-Osaka Station\n| native_name = \u65b0\u5927\u962a\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = JR station\n| image       = Shin Osaka Station 31.JPG\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Shinkansen tracks\n| other_name  = \n| address     = 5-16-1 Nishinakajima, [[Yodogawa-ku, Osaka]]\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|34|44|0.54|N|135|30|0.41|E|type:railwaystation_region:JP}}\n| operator    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[JR West]]\n* [[JR Central]]\n }}\n| line        = {{Plainlist|\n* [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen]]\n* [[San'y\u014d Shinkansen]]\n* [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Line]] ([[JR Kyoto Line]])\n* T\u014dkaid\u014d Line Branch (Umeda Freight Line)\n }}\n| platforms   =  \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| opened      = 1964\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \n| pass_year   = \n| services    = \n}}\n===Station layout===\n[[File:Shinosaka minami.jpg|thumb|]]\nThe JR station consists of four [[island platform]]s serving eight tracks for JR West Lines at ground level, with two [[side platform]]s and three island platforms serving eight Shinkansen tracks operated by JR Central located on the fourth level, over the platforms and tracks for the JR West Lines in the east. There was a space on the east side of former Track 18 from the opening of the station, where another platform serving current Tracks 17 and 18 is located, and the existing services shifted eastward one platform at a time (and renovations performed on each newly vacated platform), with the westernmost platform used by services on the [[Osaka Higashi Line]], was commenced by the 16 March 2019. On the north side of the station, an additional Shinkansen platform serving Track 27 was located on March 16, 2013. (This northern area was originally reserved for a connection from [[Awaji Station]] and [[J\u016bs\u014d Station]] by [[Hankyu Railway]], but these plans were later cancelled and the space unused).\n\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=1|first=2|span=2|linecol=red|linename=Haruka (train)|lineindex=''Haruka'' limited express|dir=for Kyoto, Kusatsu, and Maibara}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=red|linename=Kuroshio (train)|lineindex=''Kuroshio'' limited express |dir=to Kyoto}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=2|span=2|linecol=red|nolinkindex=Limited express trains|dir=termination platform}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=#335099|nolinkindex=Osaka Higashi Line|dir=for {{STN|Hanaten}} and {{STN|Ky\u016bh\u014dji}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=3|span=2|linecol=red|linename=Haruka (train)|lineindex=''Haruka'' limited express|dir=for {{STN|Kansai Airport}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=red|linename=Kuroshio (train)|lineindex=''Kuroshio'' limited express |dir=for {{STN|Shirahama}}, {{STN|Kii-Katsuura}} and {{STN|Shingu}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=4|span=2|linecol=red|linename=Hida (train)|lineindex=''Hida'' limited express|dir=for {{STN|Takayama}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=red|linename=Thunderbird (train)|lineindex=''Thunderbird'' limited express |dir=for {{STN|Fukui|Fukui}}, {{STN|Kanazawa}} and {{STN|Wakura-Onsen}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=5, 6|linecol=#0072bc|linename=JR Kyoto Line|dir=for {{STN|Suita|JR West}}, Takatsuki, and Kyoto}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=7, 8|span=2|linecol=#0072bc|linename=JR Kobe Line|dir=for {{STN|Osaka}}, {{STN|Amagasaki|JR West}}, {{STN|Ashiya|JR West}} and {{STN|Sannomiya|JR West}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=#fc0|linename=Fukuchiyama Line|lineindex=JR Takarazuka Line (through to the Fukuchiyama Line)|dir=local trains for {{STN|Takarazuka}} and {{STN|Shin-Sanda}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=9, 10|span=3|linecol=red|linename=Kounotori (train)|lineindex=''Kounotori'' limited express |dir=for {{STN|Fukuchiyama}} and {{STN|Kinosaki Onsen}} via the Fukuchiyama Line}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=red|linename=Super Hakuto|lineindex=''Super Hakuto'' limited express|dir=for {{STN|Chizu}} and {{STN|Tottori}} via the [[Chizu Express]] Chizu Line}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=red|nolinkindex=limited express trains and express trains|dir=to Osaka}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=20|linecol=mediumblue|linename=San'y\u014d Shinkansen|dir=''Hikari'', ''Kodama'' starting for Okayama, Hiroshima, and Hakata<br />''Mizuho'', ''Sakura'' for {{STN|Kumamoto}} and {{STN|Kagoshima-Ch\u016b\u014d}}}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=21, 22|linecol=mediumblue|nidx=San'y\u014d Shinkansen|dir=''Nozomi'', ''Hikari'', ''Kodama'' for {{STN|Okayama}}, {{STN|Hiroshima}}, and {{STN|Hakata}}<br />''Mizuho'' and ''Sakura'' for Kumamoto and Kagoshima-Ch\u016b\u014d}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|pfn=23|span=2|linecol=mediumblue|linename=T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen|dir= for Nagoya and Tokyo}}\n{{Ja-rail-linem|linecol=mediumblue|nolinkindex=San'y\u014d Shinkansen|dir=extra trains for Okayama, Hiroshima, and Hakata}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=24, 25, 26, 27|first=3|linecol=mediumblue|linename=T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen|dir=for {{STN|Nagoya}} and {{STN|Tokyo}}}}\n\n===Limited express trains===\n;for the [[Hokuriku Main Line]]\n* ''[[Thunderbird (train)|Thunderbird]]'': Osaka - {{STN|Kanazawa}}, {{STN|Wakura Onsen}}\n;for the [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Line]], and the [[Takayama Line]]\n* ''[[Hida (train)|Hida]]'': Osaka - {{STN|Takayama}}\n* ''Biwako Express'': Osaka - {{STN|Maibara}}\n;for the [[Hanwa Line]], the [[Kansai Airport Line]], and the [[Kisei Line|Kinokuni Line]]\n* ''[[Haruka (train)|Haruka]]'': Maibara, Kyoto - {{STN|Kansai Airport}}\n* ''[[Kuroshio (train)|Kuroshio]]'': Kyoto, Shin-Osaka - {{STN|Shirahama}}, {{STN|Shingu}}\n;for the [[Fukuchiyama Line]]\n* ''[[Kounotori (train)|Kounotori]]'': Shin-Osaka - {{STN|Fukuchiyama}}, {{STN|Toyooka|Hyogo}}, {{STN|Kinosaki Onsen}}\n;for the Sanin region via the [[Chizu Express]] Chizu Line\n* ''[[Super Hakuto]]'': Kyoto - {{STN|Tottori}}, {{STN|Kurayoshi}}\n\n===Adjacent stations===\n{{J-railservice start}}\n{{J-route|route=T\u014dkaid\u014d/San'y\u014d Shinkansen|col=mediumblue|f=w}}\n{{j-rserv|next={{STN|Shin-Kobe}}|previous={{STN|Kyoto}}|service=''[[Nozomi (train)|Nozomi]]''|col=Yellow}}\n{{j-rserv|next=Shin-Kobe|previous=Kyoto|service=''[[Hikari (train)|Hikari]]''|col=Red}}\n{{j-rserv|previous=Kyoto|service=''[[Kodama (train)|Kodama]]''<br>services from {{STN|Tokyo}}|col=Blue}}\n{{j-rserv|next=Shin-Kobe|service=''[[Kodama (train)|Kodama]]''<br>services from {{STN|Hakata}}|col=Blue}}\n{{j-rserv|service=''[[Mizuho (train)|Mizuho]]''|col=DarkOrange|previous=|next=Shin-Kobe}}\n{{j-rserv|service=''[[Sakura (train)|Sakura]]''|col=LightPink|previous=|next=Shin-Kobe}}\n{{J-route|route=T\u014dkaid\u014d Main Line (JR Kyoto Line)|col=#0072bc|f=w}}\n{{J-rserv|col=grey|previous=Kyoto (JR-A31)|next={{STN|Osaka}} (JR-A47)|service=''[[Super Hakuto]]''<BR>''[[Hida (train)|Hida]]''<BR>''[[Biwako Express]]''}}\n{{J-rserv|service=''[[Thunderbird (train)|Thunderbird]]''|previous=Kyoto (JR-A31)<br>{{STN|Takatsuki|Osaka|Takatsuki}} (JR-A38)|next=Osaka (JR-A47)|col=grey}}\n{{J-rserv|service=''[[Kounotori (train)|Kounotori]]''|next=Osaka (JR-A47)|col=grey}}\n{{J-rserv|service=''[[Haruka (train)|Haruka]]''|previous=Kyoto (JR-A31)<br>Takatsuki (JR-A38)|next={{STN|Tenn\u014dji}} (JR-R20)|col=grey}}\n{{J-rserv|service=''[[Kuroshio (train)|Kuroshio]]''|previous=Kyoto (JR-A31)|next={{STN|Nishikuj\u014d}} (JR-O14)<br>Tenn\u014dji (JR-R20)|col=grey}}\n{{J-rserv|service=Special Rapid Service|previous=Takatsuki (JR-A38)|next=Osaka (JR-A47)|col=#0072bc}}\n{{J-rserv|service=Rapid Service|previous={{STN|Ibaraki}} (JR-A41)|next=Osaka (JR-A47)|col=#f60}}\n{{J-rserv|service=Local|previous={{STN|Higashi-Yodogawa}} (JR-A45)|next=Osaka (JR-A47)|col=gray}}\n{{j-route|route=Osaka Higashi Line|col=#335099|f=w}}\n{{j-rserv|service=Direct Rapid Service|previous=Kita-Umeda (JR-F01)<br>(proposed)|n